[The specific aspects of this case are not included. That the adolescent
is recovering suggests strongly that this is a case of bubonic plague and
was diagnosed and treated promptly.
_Y. pestis_ infection is endemic in the southwestern USA. Introduction of
infection into wildlife occurred following the introduction of plague in
San Francisco in the early 20th century (1).
1. Lipson LG: Plague in San Francisco in 1900. The United States Marine
Hospital Service Commission to study the existence of plague in San
Francisco. Ann Intern Med 1972; 77:303-10.
- Mod.LL]
